        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h3 id=\"hive-panel\">Hive Panel</h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Hive panels are a special type of panel.\nBecause hive plots alone can plot either 2 or 3 categories of nodes,\nit can't handle situations where there are more than 3 categories of nodes.\nHere is where a panel of hive plots comes in:\neach plot in the panel handles 3 of the categories that are present.\nAs such, you will have <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||({K}\\choose{3}||)</marimo-tex> plots to plot.\nFor this reason, we don't recommend having more than 6 categories,\notherwise you'll end up with a lot of plots to look at.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "TqIu",
      "code_hash": "fb7df0e6d6a22390b44de4b38711e3bf",
      "outputs": [
        {
