    {
      "id": "ecfG",
      "code_hash": "1372f50299d17379855971476b01e7cc",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"development-pattern\">Development pattern</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The core of faceting in nxviz is to return an iterator of graphs\nthat contain either</span>\n<ol>\n<li>a subset of nodes,</li>\n<li>a subset of edges,</li>\n<li>or a subset of nodes and edges.</li>\n</ol>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Using one of the faceting functions as an example to illustrate:</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "Pvdt",
      "code_hash": "a7a00e5e1596e213e8ed0d15b65a00f1",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "error",
          "ename": "exception",
          "evalue": "An ancestor raised an exception (ModuleNotFoundError): ",
          "traceback": null
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "ZBYS",
      "code_hash": "b5beeb06ffdf50317545fe5b47a09c2b",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">The pattern is essentially to identify the exact groups that exist,\niterate over these groups,\nand yield a graph that contains any one of the aforementioned three subsets\nalongside the group.\nThat function pattern makes faceting consistent.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    }
